Statistical Tests

StatisticalTests.Rmd
library(umncvmstats)
mtcars <- datasets::mtcars |> 
  dplyr::mutate(dplyr::across(c(cyl, vs, am, gear, carb), forcats::as_factor)) |>
  dplyr::mutate(vs=forcats::fct_recode(vs, "V-shaped"="0", "straight"="1"),
                am=forcats::fct_recode(am, "automatic"="0", "manual"="1")) |>
  tibble::rownames_to_column("model") |> tibble::as_tibble()

set.seed(15)
passfail <- tidyr::tibble(score1=rnorm(50, mean=80, sd=7),
                          score2=rnorm(50, mean=85, sd=7)) |>
  dplyr::mutate(pass1=score1>80, pass2=score2>80) |>
  dplyr::mutate(across(starts_with("pass"), \(x) factor(x, levels=c(FALSE, TRUE), labels=c("fail", "pass"))))

Tests for Proportions

One Proportion Test 

one_proportion_test(vs~1, data=mtcars)
response x n proportion conf.low conf.high
vs = straight 14 32 0.44 0.28 0.61
Wilson's proportion test (two.sided), with 95% confidence intervals.

Separately by another categorical variable 

one_proportion_test(vs ~ am, data=mtcars)
response variable x n proportion conf.low conf.high
vs = straight am = manual 7 13 0.54 0.29 0.77
vs = straight am = automatic 7 19 0.37 0.19 0.59
Wilson's proportion test (two.sided), with 95% confidence intervals.

Two Proportion Test 

two_proportion_test(vs ~ am, data=mtcars)
response variable difference conf.low conf.high chisq.value p.value
vs = straight am: automatic - manual −0.17 −0.24 0.58 0.35   0.56
2-sample test for equality of proportions with continuity correction (two.sided), with 95% confidence intervals.

together in one table

Paired Proportion Test (McNemar’s)

  one_proportion_test(pass1 + pass2 ~ 1, data=passfail),
  one_proportion_test(pass2 ~ pass1, data=passfail, all_success = TRUE),
  paired_proportion_test(pass2 - pass1 ~ 1, data=passfail))
